  "bookTitle": "Elven Knight",
  "bookId": 48,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A mysterious elf who gives off an ethereal aura. She has a habit of referring to herself using the royal 'we.'",
  "personality": "She looks just like an elf from a storybook, emotionally detached and otherworldly, but in reality her heart is full of curiosity.",
  "like": "Golden candy",
  "familiarData": "Mu Rainell's true identity is a royal descendant of the legitimate elf kingdom, the nominal queen of the elf realm.\nShe was born before the demon invasion. All of her siblings and parents died on the battlefield in the decisive war against the demons.\nShe was sent alone into a sacred domain that only elves can enter, where she grew up accumulating strength and knowledge, hoping to one day reclaim the elf kingdom.\nHowever, the more she learned, the more she understood that the Kingdom Alliance's failures stemmed from internal disunity. Moreover, most elf elders chose to retreat into the forest, while the wanderers who came seeking help were mostly selfish individuals. Repeated disappointments gradually made Mu withdraw into pessimism.\nThrough her encounters with the Hand of Freedom, she grew curious about the world beyond the forest. So she boldly pretended to be kidnapped by the Hand of Freedom, giving herself a reason to leave the forest while also giving other elves a pretext to join the war.\nShe is highly knowledgeable and a master of healing magic. As a side note, the ingredients for the golden candy Mu loves cannot be produced in the sacred domain, which was yet another reason she chose to leave with the Hand of Freedom.",
  "familiarUnlockLevel": 5,
